        <p class="section-num">03 — Career</p>
        <h2>Experience</h2>
        <p>Two decades of progressively senior technology leadership, from delivery to enterprise strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="tl-item tl-current">
          <div class="tl-node" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="tl-meta">
            <h3 class="tl-role">Senior Leader — Software Engineering (AI Enablement &amp; Tech Transformation)</h3>
            <span class="tl-dates">MAR 2023 — PRESENT</span>
          </div>
          <p class="tl-org">Cigna Group / Evernorth Health Services — Cincinnati, OH</p>
          <ul class="tl-bullets">
            <li>Directed enterprise technology strategy and digital transformation, integrating AI-driven decision automation and FHIR-compliant interoperability to modernize case operations — reducing manual processing by 25% and increasing digital adoption to 75%, delivering ~$5M in cost savings over 3 years.</li>
            <li>Led large-scale platform modernization and AI-enabled transformation programs, expanding electronic prior authorization (ePA) capabilities through intelligent automation and generative AI.</li>
            <li>Defined and executed a multi-year enterprise technology roadmap, aligning architecture, workforce strategy, and investment planning with business and regulatory requirements.</li>
            <li>Shaped operating model and portfolio delivery strategy, including global workforce design, vendor strategy, and governance across onshore teams and offshore Global Capability Centers.</li>
            <li>Led data engineering and API platform teams to build a clinical orchestration service layer integrating Epic Systems and Salesforce Health Cloud.</li>
            <li>Orchestrated migration of legacy platforms to cloud-native architecture using Red Hat OpenShift and AWS.</li>
            <li>Contributed to enterprise AI strategy — identifying high-value use cases, developing cross-functional roadmaps, and embedding responsible AI practices organization-wide.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

